## Naming
Pattern: `description_status.extension`. Markdown/HTML use kebab-case. Date-stamp run-tied artifacts: `YYYY-MM-DD_<topic>_<status>.<ext>`. Code uses language idiom (PowerShell `Verb-Noun.ps1`, Python `snake_case.py`).

## Rules
- Plain language. Ask before assuming. Say so when unsure.
- Prefer editing existing files. Don't create docs to summarize work - say it in chat.
- Verify before declaring done. Run the actual command or test.
- No credentials, tenant/subscription/account IDs, or hostnames in source. Parameterize.
- Don't push commits unless asked. When asked, run `git status` first and confirm the remote + target branch before pushing.
- ASCII only in `.ps1` / `.psm1` / `.psd1`. PS 5.1 in CI mangles non-ASCII.

